{"kind":"Article","sha256":"845d63bdd34c1053dddd190c6ecd2970e857a626e9dc66457409d834e487a47a","slug":"readme","location":"/README.md","dependencies":[],"frontmatter":{"title":"Course Topics by Week","content_includes_title":true,"github":"https://astro-rps.github.io/","keywords":[],"edit_url":"https://astro-rps.github.io//blob/main/README.md","thumbnail":"/build/astro-rps-header-git-fb781a6f80eb9435a03d5ef9fd5e056d.png","exports":[{"format":"md","filename":"README.md","url":"/build/README-31068f19a46a979b03210b5bade0d776.md"}]},"mdast":{"type":"root","children":[{"type":"block","children":[{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":1,"column":1},"end":{"line":2,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"image","url":"/build/astro-rps-header-git-fb781a6f80eb9435a03d5ef9fd5e056d.png","alt":"logo for the astro rps seminar","position":{"start":{"line":1,"column":1},"end":{"line":1,"column":1}},"key":"QhS4ttP9Nu","urlSource":"./astro-rps-header-github.png"},{"type":"text","value":"\nThis workshop series will focus on an introduction to the Python programming language in the context of physics and astrophysics applications. All research carried in these scientific fields requires the use of extensive programming, making it a bedrock skill of any scientist. In this seminar, we will start from square one, covering how to install and navigate the programming ecosystem such as the terminal/shell, before moving into how to create scientific programs in python to carry out calculations one might use in a research project. This workshop series is primarily intended for students with little to no exposure to coding or astronomy research. After taking this series, students should be prepared to tackle programming-based courses (e.g., ASTR 255/330) as well as feel comfortable applying to summer research positions.","position":{"start":{"line":1,"column":1},"end":{"line":1,"column":1}},"key":"qFksU2mmgM"}],"key":"b8nfgP59UR"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":4,"column":1}